<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could=C2=A0<em>imagine</em>, reading a hea=
dline like =E2=80=9CFirst Citizens Buys $110 Billion of SVB Assets at $16.5=
 Billion Discount,=E2=80=9D that the $110 billion number was fake, and that=
 the =E2=80=9Cdiscount=E2=80=9D would reflect the=C2=A0<em>actual value of =
the assets</em>. You could imagine that the FDIC went to First Citizens and=
 said =E2=80=9Chey we got $110 billion of SVB stuff, you want it,=E2=80=9D =
and First Citizens was like =E2=80=9Chmm I don=E2=80=99t believe you for a =
minute that that stuff is worth $110 billion, but we=E2=80=99ll give you $9=
3.6=C2=A0billion for it,=E2=80=9D and the FDIC was like =E2=80=9Cyeah fine =
that=E2=80=99s fair.=E2=80=9D There is a lot of that sort of thing going ar=
ound in US regional banking recently; we have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/31439676.262437/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmN=
