319a23cBfc8091ab" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"=
_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-b=
ottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid;=
 background-color: #ccc;">Michael Roddan and Kate Clark report</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In the past, these VC firms relied on a specia=
lized credit line offered by SVB and a handful of other banks, including Fi=
rst Republic Bank, that plugged the gap between when the investors, or limi=
ted partners, commit capital to VC funds and when that cash actually arrive=
s. But the collapse of both SVB and First Republic is expected to make thes=
e loans harder to get. Big banks=E2=80=94such as JPMorgan Chase, which took=
 over First Republic=E2=80=99s business=E2=80=94are wary of extending these=
 loans, known as capital call credit lines, to the small VC firms that need=
 them most but are seen as riskier bets. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Unless some banks step in to offer the credit =
lines, small VC firms may have less ability to move quickly on startup inve=
stments, making it harder for them to compete with large firms.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s going to become more and=
 more difficult for smaller VC funds,=E2=80=9D said Dolph Hellman, a partne=
r in San Francisco with Orrick Herrington &amp; Sutcliffe who advises start=
ups and private investors on capital call credit lines. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The risk for the banks is that the investor wi=
ll renege on their commitment, which means the VC firm won=E2=80=99t be abl=
e to repay the credit line. As a result, before a bank lends money to a sma=
ll VC fund, it may want to know who its LPs are, the fund=E2=80=99s track r=
ecord and how likely it is to be able to convince investors to make good on=
 the capital call. All that work increases the time and cost of dealing wit=
h small VC funds, which don=E2=80=99t provide big lenders with a lot of ban=
g for their buck.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s tougher for the banks to=
 get their arms around who the investors in VC funds are. You=E2=80=99re re=
lying on the fact that the LPs are going to honor capital calls. It=E2=80=
=99s difficult for the banks to determine the creditworthiness of individua=
l investors or family offices,=E2=80=9D Hellman said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One possibility is that, in a weaker environme=
nt for startup investing and venture capital generally, startups will be wi=
lling to wait a few weeks to get their VC money?</p>
