le $292 million.) Nobody is updating their financial model to assume that F=
irst Citizens will have $9.52 billion of quarterly income from now on; that=
 number is sort of meaningless. But if you mark the assets very conservativ=
ely now, and they end up being worth more than your marks, your meaningless=
 one-time income is lower today, but you have positive income in *future* q=
uarters, when you want it. If you mark the assets pretty high now, and they=
 end up being worth less later, then your meaningless one-time income is hi=
gher today but your future earnings are lower. Earnings from SVB=E2=80=99s =
assets in future quarters are worth way, way, way more to First Citizens th=
an earnings from those assets today. Counterbalancing this incentive is tha=
